{"data":{"details":{"html":"<h4>Background</h4>\n<p>Our school uses a software called Celcat to manage and plan courses. While it seems rather reliable, it looks <em>really bad</em> and is barely usable on mobile. Fortunately, calendars are exposed as (styled) XML files, which makes it easy to parse them.</p>\n<p><img src=\"./celcat.png%20=250x250\"></p>\n<p>This is exactly what this app does: an Express app fetches the XML, parses and caches the result. The React app does the rest!</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4b7a41af8bc3e4b42779b639d11b5e2c/1568d/mine.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 216.53333333333333%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"mine\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/4b7a41af8bc3e4b42779b639d11b5e2c/b9e4f/mine.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4b7a41af8bc3e4b42779b639d11b5e2c/cf440/mine.png 148w,\n/static/4b7a41af8bc3e4b42779b639d11b5e2c/d2d38/mine.png 295w,\n/static/4b7a41af8bc3e4b42779b639d11b5e2c/b9e4f/mine.png 590w,\n/static/4b7a41af8bc3e4b42779b639d11b5e2c/f9b6a/mine.png 885w,\n/static/4b7a41af8bc3e4b42779b639d11b5e2c/1568d/mine.png 1125w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h4>Challenges</h4>\n<p>This is not a very complicated project, however it proved useful as a playground to test things such as server-side rendering and progressive web apps.</p>\n<h4>Features</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>calendar API + React app</li>\n<li>server caching</li>\n<li><strong>calendar customization</strong>: specific subjects (optional courses for instance) can be hidden</li>\n<li>offline access using local storage and <strong>server-side rendering</strong></li>\n<li><strong>mobile friendly</strong>: fully responsive, can be installed as a PWA</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"Emploi du temps Centrale","tags":["edt-ecn","javascript","react","ssr"],"description":"A timetable for the students of Centrale Nantes, designed to be fast and easy to use.","url":"https://edt-ecn.herokuapp.com","repository":{"owner":"xou816","name":"edt-ecn"}}},"github":{"repository":{"ref":{"target":{"__typename":"GitHub_Commit","abbreviatedOid":"281ceff","url":"https://github.com/xou816/edt-ecn/commit/281ceff247a9f5872d8fb826fcfd73f7b9ba6cf6","committedDate":"2019-03-18T16:17:31Z","message":"fix issue when no subjects are specified","author":{"name":"Alexandre Trendel"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/projects/edt-ecn/","repoOwner":"xou816","repoName":"edt-ecn"}}